{"actual_usd":0.15839,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":174,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31156,"reply":"\"I don't think so.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the square where the morning light is catching on the well chain.* \"If it was only an inner experience, Christianity starts to come apart at the seams pretty fast.\"\n\n\"The whole claim is that Jesus actually rose — not just that the disciples felt newly brave or had some powerful vision.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees a moment.* \"A vision can explain sincerity. It does a worse job explaining why they preached resurrection the way they did — as something God had done in history, in the body, not just in their hearts.\"\n\n\"And honestly, the physical part matters to me theologically too.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"If death only got answered symbolically, that's a very different gospel. The Christian hope isn't 'the meaning survived.' It's that Christ did.\"","rolling_24h_usd":82.99803499999999,"run_id":"48415c4c-cfdd-49a1-b952-e622e4db3086"}
